m / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))#\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = (remaining >= item)\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = remaining[can_fit]\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 2: First Fit Heuristic\nThis function assigns higher priority to bins that have been filled first.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    filled = bins > 0\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[filled] = bins[filled]\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 3: Item Fits in Bin\nThis function calculates the remaining space in each bin and assigns higher priority to bins where the item fits.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = remaining[can_fit]\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 4: Exponential Decay\nThis function uses an exponential decay function to prioritize bins with smaller remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = np.exp(-remaining[can_fit]/item)\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 5: Sine Function\nThis function uses a sine function to calculate the priority based on the remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = np.sin(np.pi * (remaining[can_fit]/item))\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 6: Cosine Function\nThis function uses a cosine function to calculate the priority based on the remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = np.cos(np.pi * (remaining[can_fit]/item))\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 7: Combined Functions\nThis function combines exponential and sine functions to calculate the priority.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = np.exp(-remaining[can_fit]/item) + np.sin(np.pi * (remaining[can_fit]/item))\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 8: Variance-Based Priority\nThis function calculates the priority based on the variance of the remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = np.var(remaining[can_fit])\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 9: Std-Based Priority\nThis function calculates the priority based on the standard deviation of the remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = np.std(remaining[can_fit])\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 10: Custom Heuristic\nThis function uses a custom combination of functions to calculate the priority.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    can_fit = remaining >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[can_fit] = (np.exp(-remaining[can_fit]/item) + np.sin(np.pi * (remaining[can_fit]/item))) * np.std(remaini