n    remaining = bins - np.mean(bins)  # This is just an example; adjust as needed\n    # Compute a priority based on how well the item fits\n    priority = np.exp(item / (remaining + 1e-8)) * np.sin(item * remaining)\n    return priority\n\n### Final Note:\nThe functions provided are examples. You need to generate 10 unique functions that follow the given constraints and use unique combinations of operations.\n\n### Start Writing the Functions\n</think>\n\nHere are 10 unique implementations of the `priority` function for the bin packing heuristic:\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * np.mean(bins) + np.sin(item) * np.std(bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item) * np.mean(bins) + np.cos(item) * np.std(bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - np.mean(bins)) * np.sin(np.pi * item)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item + 1) * np.mean(bins) + np.cos(np.pi * item)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * (np.mean(bins) - np.std(bins)) + np.sin(item)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item) * np.mean(bins) + np.cos(item) * np.var(bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * np.mean(bins) + np.sin(item) * np.var(bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item + 1) * np.mean(bins) + np.cos(item)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - np.mean(bins)) * np.sin(item) * np.cos(item)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item) * np.mean(bins) + np.cos(